## Architecture Summary

The pi agent is a CLI coding assistant. Extensions hook into its lifecycle via `ExtensionAPI`:

1. **`before_agent_start`** — inject system prompt, set active tools
2. **`tool_call`** — block/allow/modify tool invocations
3. **`tool_result`** — observe results (cache-safe, no modification)
4. **`registerTool`** — create custom tools
5. **`registerCommand`** — create slash commands
6. **`sendMessage`** — emit custom messages into chat

The orchestrator extension puts the agent into "delegate-only" mode:
- Main agent can only call `delegate(specialist, task)`
- Subagents get isolated sessions with restricted tool sets (scout=read+bash, coder=read+bash+edit+write, etc.)
- Scope-guard enforces file boundaries from scout's analysis
- Plan panel + activity feed provide real-time TUI visualization

